About
=====

This software is part of the GNU Project. On computers with an ICH9
Southbridge, the boot flash can have a partition table and some
partitions in it.

Here this can generate the data that goes inside the partition table
and the Gigabit Ethernet partition.

Why?
====

This could also have been moved within Guix package in GNU Boot,
however adding the proper boilierplate to use autotools and so on
enable to have something that can also be packaged by other
distributions as well with less efforts.

History
=======

This software was written to replace the ich9utils program written for
Libreboot with bincfg and ifdtool which enables to have more
fine-grained control over the generated files.

At first the goal was to generate the exact same files to provide a
drop-in replacement before being able to modify the files to catch up
with Coreboot settings.

